==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Paten
<hw>Pat"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL. <ets>patina</ets>,
<ets>patena</ets>, fr. L. <ets>patina</ets>, <ets>patena</ets>, a pan;
cf. L. <ets>patere</ets> to be open, E. <ets>patent</ets>, and Gr.
<grk>pata`nh</grk> a kind of flat dish: cf. F. <ets>pat⟦egrave⟧ne</ets>.
Cf. <er>Patina</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A plate.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The place on which the
consecrated bread is placed in the Eucharist, or on which the host is
placed during the Mass. It is usually small, and formed as to fit the
chalice, or cup, as a cover.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><altsp>[Written also <asp>patin</asp>,
<asp>patine</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Patena</ent>⟦br⟧
